6 Section 2. Section 49-2-101, MCA, is amended to read:
7 "49-2-101. Definitions. As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise, the following
8 definitions apply:
9 (1) "Age" means number of years since birth. It does not mean level of maturity or ability to handle
10 responsibility. These latter criteria may represent legitimate considerations as reasonable grounds for
11 discrimination without reference to age.
12 (2) "Aggrieved party" means a person who can demonstrate a specific personal and legal interest,
13 as distinguished from a general interest, and who has been or is likely to be specially and injuriously affected by
14 a violation of this chapter.
15 (3) "Commission" means the commission for human rights provided for in 2-15-1706.
16 (4) "Commissioner" means the commissioner of labor and industry provided for in 2-15-1701.
17 (5) "Controversial social vision" means any agenda, concept, or theory that promotes concepts,
18 ideas, or issues that are not broadly accepted in society or that generate strong opposition by mainstream
19 political, religious, or social groups with the various facts or theories being in dispute.
20 (6) "Credit" means the right granted by a creditor to a person to defer payment of a debt, to incur
21 debt and defer its payment, or to purchase property or services and defer payment. It includes without limitation
22 the right to incur and defer debt that is secured by residential real property.
23 (7) "Credit transaction" means any invitation to apply for credit, application for credit, extension of
24 credit, or credit sale.
25 (8) "Creditor" means a person who, regularly or as a part of the person's business, arranges for
26 the extension of credit for which the payment of a financial charge or interest is required, whether in connection
27 with loans, sale of property or services, or otherwise.
28 (9) "Department" means the department of labor and industry provided for in 2-15-1701.
